sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as NotebookWebhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as OpenshiftNotebookReconciler<br/>Controller
    participant KFController as Kubeflow Notebook Controller
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Notebook as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    %% Flow 1: Notebook Creation with OAuth
    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Creation with OAuth

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: AdmissionReview<br/>Auth: mTLS (API server cert)
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject OAuth sidecar config<br/>Add reconciliation lock annotation
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Return mutated CR<br/>Auth: mTLS
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Notify: Notebook created/updated<br/>Auth: Service Account Token

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>with OAuth redirect ref<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Secret<br/>(OAuth config, cookie secret)<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service (OAuth)<br/>443→8443 HTTPS<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service (Base)<br/>80→8888 HTTP<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route<br/>Edge TLS termination<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap<br/>(Trusted CA bundle)<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Patch Notebook CR<br/>(remove lock annotation)<br/>Auth: Service Account Token

    K8sAPI->>KFController: Notify: Notebook updated
    KFController->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>with injected OAuth sidecar<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook CR created

    %% Flow 2: Notebook Access (OAuth Enabled)
    Note over Browser,Notebook: Flow 2: Notebook Access (OAuth Enabled)

    Browser->>Router: GET https://{route-url}<br/>No auth
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+

    alt User not authenticated
        OAuthProxy->>Browser: Redirect to OAuth login
        Browser->>OAuthServer: OAuth authentication flow<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
        OAuthServer-->>Browser: OAuth token
        Browser->>Router: Request with OAuth cookie
        Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward with cookie
    end

    OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Check GET permission on Notebook CR<br/>Auth: User OAuth token
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Authorization result

    alt User authorized
        OAuthProxy->>Notebook: Proxy request<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (plaintext)
        Notebook-->>OAuthProxy: Response
        OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS response
        Router-->>Browser: HTTPS response<br/>TLS1.3
    else User not authorized
        OAuthProxy-->>Browser: 403 Forbidden
    end

    %% Flow 3: Controller Reconciliation
    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Controller Reconciliation (Watch Loop)

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CRs<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Notebook event<br/>(create/update/delete)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Reconcile resources<br/>(Route, Service, Secret, etc.)<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Update Notebook status<br/>Auth: Service Account Token
